# UI Components Guidelines

## GlassCard Component

The GlassCard widget should be used for all card-like containers in the app. It provides a consistent glassmorphism effect with the following properties:

- Semi-transparent background
- Blur effect
- Subtle border
- Rounded corners

## Tile Component

The Tile widget represents game tiles and should follow these guidelines:

- Color coding based on value:
  - 1: Blue (#3B82F6)
  - 2: Red (#EF4444)
  - 3+: White (#FFFFFF) with black text
- Consistent size across the board
- Animation capabilities:
  - New tile animation
  - Merge animation
  - Movement animation
- Proper text scaling for larger numbers

## Button Styles

Use the GlowButton component for all interactive buttons with these properties:

- Hover/press glow effect
- Consistent padding
- Icon + text layout when appropriate
- Appropriate color based on action type:
  - Primary actions: Purple gradient
  - Secondary actions: Glass effect

## Text Styles

- Headings: Bold, large font size (24-48px)
- Body text: Regular weight, medium size (16-18px)
- Labels: Medium weight, smaller size (14px)
- Score numbers: Bold, large size (32-48px)

## Layout Components

- Use consistent container padding (16-24px)
- Maintain proper spacing between elements
- Ensure touch targets are at least 44x44 points
- Use flexible layouts that adapt to different screen sizes